text: Josep Corominas i Busqueta (24 March 1939 – 30 December 2020) was a Spanish physician and politician. He was a member of the Congress of Deputies from 1989 and 2000. He also was Grand Master of the Spain's Grand Lodge from 2002 and 2006. Corominas i Busqueta died in Barcelona on 30 December 2020 at the age of 81.Mor Josep Corominas i Busqueta, president de l’Ateneu Terrassenc i exregidor de l’Ajuntament de Terrassa ==References== Category:1939 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Spanish politicians Category:Spanish physicians
